cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of Bayesian Neural Networks for classification and regression problems, which are common topics in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of probabilistic programming libraries, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The combination of neural networks and stochastic models also suggests a potential overlap with the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's discussion of generating probabilistic guarantees on predictions suggests a potential overlap with the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY).
